<P>What the Pope had formerly done, the barons thought proper to do now; they offered the crown of England to France, and Philip accepted it with joy; but, fearing the Pope's di&s;plea&s;ure, he prevailed on the Engli&s;h barons to elect his &s;on Louis. In this they agreed, and the city of London lent it's a&s;&s;i&s;tance. Louis landed in England with a large army, in 1216; John was depo&s;ed, and Louis was crowned at London; which &s;o affected John's &s;pirits that it occa&s;ioned his death the &s;ame year, in the fifty fir&s;t year of his age, after having reigned &s;eventeen years.</P>
