<P>He was &s;ucceeded in 1307, by his fourth &s;on, Edward II. By his mal-admini&s;traction, and countenancing &s;ome favourites in oppo&s;ition to the barons, he brought on a civil war; battles were fought, many noble pri&s;oners ta|ken on both &s;ides, and the &s;caffolds were drenched with
