<P>James began his reign by labouring to unite both king|doms into one, but the jealou&s;y of the Engli&s;h put a &s;t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> to it for the pre&s;ent, le&s;t the offices in the Engli&s;h co<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> and government &s;hould be di&s;po&s;ed of to Scotchmen.</P>
