<P>In &s;ome mea&s;ure he did. The bodies of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">omwell and &s;ome others, were taken from their graves, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">agged to the place of execution, and there hung up a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">ole day, and afterwards buried under the gallows, and, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">t of eighty per&s;ons then living, and concerned in the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ath of Charles I. ten were executed. Had Charles II. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">en an active monarch, he might have been an ab&s;olute <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">e; for the parliament was all obedience; but, in&s;tead <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> de&s;iring an a&s;cendency over them, he was content to be <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> humble dependant on their bounty.</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<PB N="70" REF="75">
