<P>Very much &s;o: he kept &s;everal mi&s;tre&s;&s;es and enobled them all. From the&s;e have &s;prung &s;everal of o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> noble families, the dukes of St. Alban, Grafton, an<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Richmond. As the king was not married, and his bro|ther James, duke of York, was a declared papi&s;t, the parliament pa&s;&s;ed a law to exclude him from the throne but notwith&s;tanding this, on the death of Charles, whi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> happened in 1684, his brother &s;ucceeded him, as James II</P>
</SP>
<SP>
