</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>ERAST.</SPEAKER>
<P>William, being an ambitious prince, all his <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">ons were levelled at power, and he no &s;ooner received <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> invitation to come over to England with an army, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">in he equipped a fleet &s;ufficient to tran&s;port 15,000 men. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">mes now &s;aw his errors and would have retracted his <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">a&s;ures in favour of popery, but it was too late. Wil|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">m &s;ailed from Holland and landed at Torbay, in De|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">n&s;hire, with 13,000 troops. The people joined him <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">d the nobility who formed the court and council of king <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">mes, left their old ma&s;ter to &s;olicit protection from the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">w.</P>
</SP>
<SP>
