</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>ERAST.</SPEAKER>
<P>The Humming bird. This bird, &s;o com|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">on in America, e&s;pecially the male, is a ma&s;ter-piece <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">f nature. It is wonderful, not only in the variety and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">reline&s;s of its colours, but al&s;o in the littlene&s;s of its
<PB N="100" REF="181">body. It is not bigger than a &s;mall nut. There is in Canada a &s;pecies &s;till &s;maller, called the Bird-fly; which is not larger than a great fly. Its flight, how|ever, is extremely rapid. Could you &s;uppo&s;e it? This &s;mall bird will attack a crow, and beat it down from the middle of the air. It is &s;o beautiful a bird, that the Indians make ear-rings of it.</P>
